"title": "8605: prayer, and God's will",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "8605",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>Prayer is concerned not only with the well-being of the one who prays. A vital aspect of its purpose is to allow the will of God to be done, and to bring glory and honour to his name.</p>\n<h2>True motives for prayer</h2>\n<h3>The desire that God's name be honoured</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt6:9-Matt6:13\">MAT 6:9–6:13</a></strong> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke11:2-Luke11:4\">LUK 11:2–11:4</a> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num14:13-Num14:16\">NUM 14:13–14:16</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Josh7:7-Josh7:9\">JOS 7:7–7:9</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam7:25-2Sam7:26\">2SA 7:25–7:26</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs18:36-1Kgs18:37\">1KI 18:36–18:37</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps115:1\">PSA 115:1</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John17:1\">JHN 17:1</a></p>\n<h3>The desire that God's will be fulfilled</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt6:9-Matt6:13\">MAT 6:9–6:13</a></strong> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke11:2-Luke11:4\">LUK 11:2–11:4</a> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt26:39\">MAT 26:39</a> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark14:36\">MRK 14:36</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke22:42\">LUK 22:42</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt26:42\">MAT 26:42</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb10:7\">HEB 10:7</a> <em>Submission to God's will characterised Jesus Christ's prayer life.</em></p>\n<h2>God answers prayer that accords with his will</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1John5:14-1John5:15\">1JN 5:14–5:15</a></strong></p>\n<h3>Petitioners may enquire of God to discover his will</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps143:10\">PSA 143:10</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen25:22-Gen25:23\">GEN 25:22–25:23</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Judg1:1-Judg1:2\">JDG 1:1–1:2</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam2:1\">2SA 2:1</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Chr14:14-1Chr14:15\">1CH 14:14–14:15</a></p>\n<h3>The Holy Spirit helps believers to pray in God's will</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom8:26-Rom8:27\">ROM 8:26–8:27</a></strong></p>\n<h2>God's response to prayers allows believers to discern his will</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Cor12:7-2Cor12:9\">2CO 12:7–12:9</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod33:18-Exod33:20\">EXO 33:18–33:20</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam12:15-2Sam12:18\">2SA 12:15–12:18</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job19:7-Job19:8\">JOB 19:7–19:8</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps35:13-Ps35:14\">PSA 35:13–35:14</a></p>\n<h2>God does not respond to the prayers of the wicked</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/John9:31\">JHN 9:31</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps66:18\">PSA 66:18</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov15:8\">PRO 15:8</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa1:15\">ISA 1:15</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa59:1-Isa59:2\">ISA 59:1–59:2</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lam3:44\">LAM 3:44</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Pet3:12\">1PE 3:12</a></p>",
